Package com.pranab.playwithgraphs.weightedgraphs

Class WeightedNode<V,​K,​W extends Weight>

java.lang.Object
com.pranab.playwithgraphs.weightedgraphs.WeightedNode<V,​K,​W>
Type Parameters:
V - - The value of object to be maintained in the Graph's Node/Vertex.
K - - Keys of target node to store the relationships associated with a node.
W - - An entity that implements Weight so as to simulate strength of relationship as integer values.
Direct Known Subclasses:
DirectedWeightedNode, UnDirectedWeightedNode
public class WeightedNode<V,​K,​W extends Weight>
extends java.lang.Object
The object of this class is basic building unit i.e. Node/Vertex for Weighted Graphs.
Configured to accommodate the weight for weighted edges. It maintains the properties:
value - The value that needs to be preserved.
traversed - A boolean property depicting weather node has been traversed or not.
outGoingEdges - Stores the edges from this node to other nodes
Author:
Pranab Bharadwaj
